The paper discusses knowledge graph completion using embedding models, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves working with structured data and databases, which can be categorized under database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing models and proposes a new approach, which can be categorized under natural language processing (cs.CL).
